    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I'm getting this now and the solution looks to be the same one proposed here.\r\n\r\n```\r\nERROR in .../node_modules/instantsearch.js/es/lib/InstantSearch.d.ts(94,97):\r\n94:97 Type 'typeof EventEmitter' is not a constructor function type.\r\n    92 |  * It emits the 'render' event every time a search is done\r\n    93 |  */\r\n  > 94 | declare class InstantSearch<TUiState extends UiState = UiState, TRouteState = TUiState> extends EventEmitter {\r\n       |                                                                                                 ^\r\n    95 |     client: InstantSearchOptions['searchClient'];\r\n    96 |     indexName: string;\r\n    97 |     insightsClient: AlgoliaInsightsClient | null;\r\n```\r\n\r\nBoth on Typescript 3.8.3 and 4.5.2 (this error message from 4.5.2). This also came up here: https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/issues/4911 and required a different workaround. We're consuming this through vue-instantsearch.\r\n\r\nI was just coming here to open this same PR to unblock our usage. Looks like we'll need to fork with this fix unless we can bring it in here.",
