    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Aaaand now when I try to build my fork I get the following build error: \r\n\r\n```\r\n[!] Error: 'EventEmitter' is not exported by node_modules/events/events.js\r\nhttps://rollupjs.org/guide/en/#error-name-is-not-exported-by-module\r\nsrc/lib/InstantSearch.ts (3:9)\r\n1: import type { AlgoliaSearchHelper } from 'algoliasearch-helper';\r\n2: import algoliasearchHelper from 'algoliasearch-helper';\r\n3: import { EventEmitter } from 'events';\r\n            ^\r\n4: import type { IndexWidget } from '../widgets/index/index';\r\n5: import index, { isIndexWidget } from '../widgets/index/index';\r\nError: 'EventEmitter' is not exported by node_modules/events/events.js\r\n    at error (/Users/jeff/workspace/instantsearch.js/node_modules/rollup/dist/rollup.js:5330:30)\r\n    at Module.error (/Users/jeff/workspace/instantsearch.js/node_modules/rollup/dist/rollup.js:9733:16)\r\n    at handleMissingExport (/Users/jeff/workspace/instantsearch.js/node_modules/rollup/dist/rollup.js:9634:28)\r\n    at Module.traceVariable (/Users/jeff/workspace/instantsearch.js/node_modules/rollup/dist/rollup.js:10072:24)\r\n    at ModuleScope.findVariable (/Users/jeff/workspace/instantsearch.js/node_modules/rollup/dist/rollup.js:8679:39)\r\n    at Identifier$1.bind (/Users/jeff/workspace/instantsearch.js/node_modules/rollup/dist/rollup.js:4353:40)\r\n    at CallExpression$1.bind (/Users/jeff/workspace/instantsearch.js/node_modules/rollup/dist/rollup.js:3098:31)\r\n    at CallExpression$1.bind (/Users/jeff/workspace/instantsearch.js/node_modules/rollup/dist/rollup.js:6631:15)\r\n    at VariableDeclarator.bind (/Users/jeff/workspace/instantsearch.js/node_modules/rollup/dist/rollup.js:3102:23)\r\n    at VariableDeclaration.bind (/Users/jeff/workspace/instantsearch.js/node_modules/rollup/dist/rollup.js:3098:31)\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhich is the same error referenced in https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/issues/2730. So indeed it looks like we have two competing environments that demand different import structures...\r\n\r\nI upgraded node on my local machine from `v16.8.0` to `v17.0.1` and upgraded `@types/node` and it seemed to resolve the issue \r\n",
