  {
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@Haroenv thanks for your fast follow up. Setting `esModuleInterop: true` resolves this error but opens up many other issues. I haven't been able to reproduce the problem in a minimal example yet, so I'm diving more deeply (I haven't worked with typescript in a few years). \r\n\r\nHopefully I can get you something to work with soon. In my big baggy repo I get:\r\n\r\n```\r\nyarn run v1.22.17\r\n$ tsc\r\npnode_modules/instantsearch.js/es/lib/InstantSearch.d.ts:94:97 - error TS2507: Type 'typeof EventEmitter' is not a constructor function type.\r\n\r\n94 declare class InstantSearch<TUiState extends UiState = UiState, TRouteState = TUiState> extends EventEmitter {\r\n                                                                                                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\nFound 1 error.\r\n\r\nerror Command failed with exit code 2.\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn my environment, changing `import EventEmitter from 'events';` to `import { EventEmitter } from 'events'` resolves the issue. Can someone help me understand why `events` is showing unpredictable behavior here? ",
